// Read and write of CIA model value using the following simple format
// to send SPI command sequences to the flash chip and report status:
//
// control [SPI_command [A23-A16 A15-A8 A7-A0 [D7-D0]]] ...
//
// Where the control byte format is as follows:
//
// Bits
//  7    1 = Repeat command until read data bit 0 = 0 (for command 05h)
//  6    1 = Output data bit 0 to erase status bit (for command 05h after 20h)
//  5    1 = Output data bit 0 to program status bit (for command 05h after 02h)
//  4    1 = Read a single data byte at end of command
//  3:0  Count of bytes in command
//
// The command sequence ends when control = 0.

// BRAM offset = 0:
// 1. 03h Read Data (first byte in 4K block #31)
// 2. End
14  03 01 F0 00
00

// BRAM offset = 6:
// 1. 06h Write Enable
// 2. 20h Block Erase (4K block #31)
// 3. 05h Read Status Register 1, output BUSY bit to erase status bit, repeat until BUSY bit is cleared
// 4. 06h Write Enable
// 5. 02h Page Program (first byte in first page in 4K block #31)
// 6. 05h Read Status Register 1, output BUSY bit to program status bit, repeat until BUSY bit is cleared
// 7. End
01  06
04  20 01 F0 00
D1  05
01  06
05  02 01 F0 00 FF  // Data byte (BRAM offset = 22) must be set to CIA model value
B1  05
00
